{%- comment -%}
	Renders the info tooltip used in the versus-comparator section.

	Accepts:
	- content: richtext — tooltip content
	- image: image_picker — optional image shown in the tooltip
	- variant: 'inline' to reduce the icon size (12px) for inline use (e.g. after a subtitle)
	- cs_class: optional ContentSquare tracking class appended to the trigger span
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%}
	The whole tooltip is wrapped in a <span> so it can be inlined inside an rte <p>. Rich-text
	`content` from the editor often comes wrapped in <p>...</p> tags — those <p> blocks would
	break the parent inline flow (browsers auto-close the outer <p> when they meet a <p> inside
	a <span>). We strip the outer <p> wrappers and turn line breaks into <br> so the tooltip
	stays valid inline HTML.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if content != blank -%}
	{%- liquid
		# Strip <p> wrappers and turn paragraph breaks into <br> so a single inline string remains.
		assign tooltip_text = content | replace: '<p>', '' | replace: '</p>', '<br>'
		# Trim trailing <br> left over from the final </p> (Liquid has no replace_last filter).
		assign tooltip_tail = tooltip_text | slice: -4, 4
		if tooltip_tail == '<br>'
			assign tooltip_text_len = tooltip_text.size | minus: 4
			assign tooltip_text = tooltip_text | slice: 0, tooltip_text_len
		endif
	-%}
	<span
		class="tooltip ax-versus-comparator__tooltip{% if variant == 'inline' %} ax-versus-comparator__tooltip--inline{% endif %}{% if cs_class != blank %} {{ cs_class }}{% endif %}"
		tabindex="0"
		role="button"
		aria-describedby=""
	>
		{{- 'icon-info.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}
		<span class="tooltip-content" role="tooltip">
			{%- if image != blank -%}
				{{ image | image_url: height: 80 | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', alt: '' }}
			{%- endif -%}
			<span class="ax-versus-comparator__tooltip-text">{{ tooltip_text }}</span>
		</span>
	</span>
{%- endif -%}
